  "time_ut": 1657535619,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd4  \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Parliamentary committee meetings stopped",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Considering the current situation in the country, the committee meetings of the Parliament have also been temporarily stopped.",
        "Ceylon Petroleum Statutory Corporation, Ceylon Petroleum Storage Terminal Company and the chairpersons of the Public Utilities Commission were scheduled to be called before the Committee on Public Enterprises (COPE Committee) of the Parliament tomorrow (12) at 10.00 am, but due to the current political situation in the country, it was decided not to hold the meeting. That was done by the Chairman of the Committee, Member of Parliament Professor Charita Herath.",
        "Due to the private statement made by the Chairman of Sri Lanka Public Utilities Commission in the last COP committee meeting, a great controversy arose in the country regarding the price of petroleum. Accordingly, the COPE Committee had decided to invite the Chairman of the Public Utilities Commission of Sri Lanka and the heads of the Petroleum Statutory Corporation to investigate the matter.",
        "Mr. Charathi Herath further said that it was decided to hold the COP committee meeting after the situation in the country calmed down."
      ],
